                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>Possibly Samuel van Huls, The Hague, sold; [Jan Swart, The Hague, 14 May 1736, Port. O, lot 691.]  Possibly Nourri, sold; [Paris, Folliot, Regnault, c.p. Brusley, Poussin, 24 February – 14 March 1785, part of lots 891-3.] [Frederick Keppel & Co., New York] sold; to Meta and Paul J. Sachs, Cambridge, Mass. (L. 2091, without his mark); Bequest of Meta and Paul J. Sachs, 1965.226<br />
